            "answer_text": "Scattering means absorption and re-emission of the incident photon by a free electron or an electron bound to an atom. The free electrons inside a metal mirror are what causes the reflection. They oscillate 180 degrees out of phase with the incident light, leading to destructive interference of the transmitted light and therefore to complete reflection. Since there is no bandgap for free electrons, they absorb and re-emit all the photons incident on them, but since the phase of the transmitted light is opposed to the phase of the incident light, the probability for transmission of photons is zero, all get reflected. Image Acquisition Dielectric mirrors are composed of very thin layers of transparent materials with high refractive index alternating with low reflective index. This leads to the thin film interference in multiple layers, amplifying the reflection of some frequencies of light and attenuating the reflection of other frequencies. Dichroic filter - Wikipedia Thin-film interference - Wikipedia Diffuse reflection comes from incoherent scattering of light by scattering centers Diffuse reflection - Wikipedia ",
