            "answer_text": "You can have several different pictures. Physics uses mathematical models to describe nature. As long as they produce the observed results they are all valid. You may look at light as an ekectromagnetic wave. The mirror is a conducting surface and imposes boundary conditions. The incoming wave creates a currdnt and this current creates the outgoing wave. You can view it as photons. The photons are absorbed and new photons are emitted. Interference of these to cancel in all directions except the directions of the outgoing ray. You may look at photons as exitations of the photon field. Now you are back at the EM fielt. The EM field is the same as the photon field. ",
