            "answer_text": "In classical electrodynamics, reflections of waves show up at boundaries where there is a change in index of refraction due to dielectric \u201cconstant,\u201d or due to conductivity. Getting a hold on the contribution from microscopic effects and macroscopic wave behavior has a few points of contact. First is the Ewald-Oseen extinction theorem. Ewald\u2013Oseen extinction theorem - Wikipedia Second is the Clausius-Mossottti equation like arguments. http://web.hep.uiuc.edu/home/serrede/P435/Lecture_Notes/P435_Lect_12.pdf That gets you to a position where you can explore the response of polarization interactions between molecules and photons. ",
